ğŸ«´Â°Â°Â° HTML EntitiesÂ°Â°Â°âœ¨
 1. If you see < you have to escape it using &lt; or a encoding &#60;

 2. Their are four Reserved entities in HTML { <,>, &, "}> Their character reference is &lt;, &gt;, &amp;, last &quit;.

 3. A few more you may encounter are &copy; for copyright. &trade; for Trademark â„¢ï¸. &nbsp; for Non Breaking Space. Their are over 2000 names character references you can find @ "https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multi page/named-charactera.html#names-character-references"
another Great Reference is "mothereff.in" this has a multiple tools you can use in conjunction with Dev Tools.
